                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#83ra">f. 83ra</locus>
                           <desc>-rb: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#83ra">83ra-</locus>b: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ አእማደ፡ ምስጢር፡ ዘሐለቃ፡ ተስፋይ፡
                              ኰኰሎ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ገብረ፡ ስላሴ፡ {ወብእሲቱ፡ ኂሩተ፡ ስላሴ፡} ወአቡሁ፡ መዝገበ፡ ስላሴ፡ ወደቂቁ፡ ኪነ፡
                              ስላሴ፡ ሐብተ፡ ስላሴ፡ ኃይለ፡ ስላሴ፡ አመተ፡ ስላሴ፡ ወለተ፡ ስላሴ፡ ጥበበ፡ ስላሴ፡ ልሕኵተ፡ ስላሴ፡
                              ስምረተ፡ ስላሴ፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወእማ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወእህታ፡ ዓመተ፡ ጽዮን፡ ወወለታ፡ ወለተ፡
                              ብርሃን፡ ወእሁኁ፡ ገብረ፡ ጊዎርጊስ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ኃለቃ፡ አባይ፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሀቆ፡ ወዘተአገሎ፡ በኃይል፡
                              ዘዕ{ን}በለ፡ ፈቃደ፡ እግዚኡ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በስልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮ{ስ}፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ከመ፡ አርዮስ፡
                              ወመቅደልዮስ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#83ra">83ra-</locus>b: This book of ʾAʿmāda mǝśṭir is
                              of ḥaläqa Tasfāyä [of] Kʷäkʷälo, who is Gabra Śǝllāse. {His wife is
                              Ḫiruta Śǝllāse} and his father Mazgaba Śǝllāse, and his children Kinä
                              Śǝllāse, Habta Śǝllāse, Ḫāyla Śǝllāse, ʾAmata Śǝllāse, Walatta
                              Śǝllāse, Ṭǝbäbä Śǝllāse, Lǝḥkʷǝtä Śǝllāse, Sǝmrätä Śǝllāse, and his
                              mother Walatta ʾƎgziʾ, and her mother Walatta Māryām, and her sister
                              ʿĀmata Ṣǝyon, and her daughter Walatta Bǝrhān, and his brother Gabra
                              Giyorgis that is ḫaläqa ʾAbbay. May the one who stole it or erased it
                              or took it by force without the permission of the owner be
                              excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul like Arius and
                              Macedonius. </quote> The note contains a tämäläs-sign, in the shape of
                           two perpendicular lines, indicating where the omission, written above,
                           belongs: <locus target="#83ra">83ra</locus>
                           <note> l.8. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters, words and passages are written
                           interlineally, in the main hand: <locus target="#6vb">6vb</locus>, 46rb,
                           57ra, 68vb, 80vb.
 - Erasure of words: <locus target="#9va">9va</locus>, 17va, 19rb, 24ra, 25vb, 43va, 44rb, 45vb, 46va, 47ra,
                           49va, 59ra, 60ra, 61ra, 66ra, 67vb.
 - Interlinear corrections:
                              <locus target="#19v">19v</locus>, 57ra, 68vb, 70va, 71vb.
 - A
                           crude note: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
